<TITLE> Janajuddho leader slain in Pabna </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, August 4 (bdnews24.com)  A leader of a faction of the banned extremist outfit Purbo Banglar Communist Party was shot and killed on Monday, allegedly by assailants from a rival group, police said. The deceased was identified as 35 year-old Shahidul Islam, a leader of PBCP's Marxist-Leninist Janajuddho faction. Around 10 individuals abducted Shahidul Islam from his house in Laxmipur village under Sathiya upazila on Monday night, Pabna police superintendent Nibash Chandra Majhi, told bdnews24.com. Police recovered Islam's body from Mongolgram in Faridpur Upazila on Tuesday. Several cases, including one for murder, were outstanding against Islam at different police stations in Pabna, police said. A case has been filed at Faridpur Police Station in connection with the incident. Police are yet to make any arrests. bd
